\title{Devices and Color}
\author{bmorphism}
\import{macros}
\date{2026-03-29}
\taxon{reference}

\p{The hardware layer of the BCI Factory ([[horse-0001]]).}

\subtree{
\title{SplitMix64 Color Hash}
\p{Every name maps to a hue via SplitMix64 deterministic hash. Seed the RNG with the name, extract a 64-bit state, map to HSL hue. 1.7M colors/sec on commodity hardware. The color is your Rider identity — computed, not chosen.}

\p{Implementation: Gay.jl \code{color_at(seed)} with \code{splitmix64_next} producing the raw state.}
}

\subtree{
\title{EEG: OpenBCI Cyton 8ch}
\p{250Hz sample rate. 8 electrodes define the Grothendieck topology ([[horse-0002]]). The montage is the site — the topological structure on which all sheaves live.}
}

\subtree{
\title{fNIRS}
\p{Near-infrared spectroscopy measures HbO/HbR concentration. Natural GF(3) encoding: HbO = +1, HbR = -1, baseline = 0. Cross-modal fusion with EEG via tensor product of sheaves.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Eye Tracking}
\p{120Hz gaze position defines the attention functor ([[horse-0005]]). Regions under fixation get higher decode priority.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Device Inventory}
\p{See [[horse-0001]] for current status. Primary: Cyton 8ch (shared) at 222 Dore St.}
}
